math.geom2d
Class CircleArc2D

java.lang.Object
  math.geom2d.EllipseArc2D
      math.geom2d.CircleArc2D
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.awt.Shape, ContinuousCurve2D, ContinuousOrientedCurve2D, Curve2D, OrientedCurve2D, Shape2D, SmoothCurve2D
public class CircleArc2D
extends EllipseArc2D

A circle arc. It is defined by the center and the radius of the containing circle, and by two angles: the first angle is the beginning of the arc, the second angle is the signed angle extent.

A circle arc is directed: angle extent is counted positively counter clockwise if arc is direct, or clockwise if arc is indirect.

A circle arc is parameterized using angle from center. The arc contains all points with a parametric equation of t, for each t between 0 and the angle extent.

Author:
dlegland
